                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract93-1">
                        <quote source="#bib93-1">Metropolitan of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/193">Tagrit</placeName>.</quote></note>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="description">In hagiography: Marutha of Tagrit was born near <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/42">Balad</placeName> and 
                        became a monk of the monastery of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/356">Mar Zakkay</placeName> and then at <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/227">Mor Matay</placeName>. 
                        He became the first Maphrian of the Syrian Orthodox Church in the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/150">Sasanian empire</placeName>.</note>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="deprecation" xml:id="name93-5-deprecation">Dolabani's spelling of "Marutha" in Syriac should have an 'a' vowel instead of an 'e' 
                        vowel at the end: ܡܰܪܘܬܶܐ ܕܬܰܓܪܝܬ.</note>
